31  import java.nio.CharBuffer;
32  import java.nio.ByteBuffer;
33  import java.nio.charset.Charset;
34  import java.nio.charset.CharsetDecoder;
35  import java.nio.charset.CharsetEncoder;
36  import java.nio.charset.CoderResult;
37  import sun.nio.cs.HistoricallyNamedCharset;
38  import sun.nio.cs.Surrogate;
39  import sun.nio.cs.ext.*;
40  
41  public class IBM949_OLD
42      extends Charset
43      implements HistoricallyNamedCharset
44  {
45  
46      public IBM949_OLD() {
47          super("x-IBM949-Old", null);
48      }
49  
50      public String historicalName() {
51          return "Cp949";
52      }
53  
54      public boolean contains(Charset cs) {
55          return (cs instanceof IBM949);
56      }
57  
58      public CharsetDecoder newDecoder() {
59          return new Decoder(this);
60      }
61  
62      public CharsetEncoder newEncoder() {
63          return new Encoder(this);
64      }
65  
66  
67      /**
68       * These accessors are temporarily supplied while sun.io
69       * converters co-exist with the sun.nio.cs.{ext} charset coders
70       * These facilitate sharing of conversion tables between the
71       * two co-existing implementations. When sun.io converters
72       * are made extinct these will be unncessary and should be removed
73       */
74  
75      public String getDecoderSingleByteMappings() {
76          return Decoder.singleByteToChar;
77  
78      }
79  
80      public short[] getDecoderIndex1() {
81          return Decoder.index1;
82      }
83  
84      public String getDecoderIndex2() {
85          return Decoder.index2;
86  
87      }
88  
89      public short[] getEncoderIndex1() {
90          return Encoder.index1;
91  
92      }
93      public String getEncoderIndex2() {
94          return Encoder.index2;
95  
96      }
97      public String getEncoderIndex2a() {
98          return Encoder.index2a;
99  
100     }
101 
102     protected static class Decoder extends DBCS_IBM_ASCII_Decoder {
103 
104         private void initLookupTables() {
105                 super.mask1 = 0xFFE0;
106                 super.mask2 = 0x001F;
107                 super.shift = 5;
108                 super.leadByte = this.leadByte;
109                 super.index1 = this.index1;
110                 super.index2 = this.index2;
111         }
112         public Decoder(Charset cs) {
113                 super(cs);
114                 initLookupTables();
115                 super.singleByteToChar = this.singleByteToChar;
116         }
117         protected Decoder(Charset cs, String singleByteToChar) {
118                 super(cs);
119                 initLookupTables();
120                 super.singleByteToChar = singleByteToChar;
121         }
122

1494     protected static class Encoder extends CharsetEncoder {
1495 
1496         private static final char SBase = '\uAC00';
1497         private static final char LBase = '\u1100';
1498         private static final char VBase = '\u1161';
1499         private static final char TBase = '\u11A7';
1500         private static final int  VCount = 21;
1501         private static final int  TCount = 28;
1502         private static final byte G0 = 0;
1503         private static final byte G1 = 1;
1504         private static final byte G2 = 2;
1505         private static final byte G3 = 3;
1506         private byte   charState = G0;
1507         private char   l, v, t;
1508 
1509         private int  mask1;
1510         private int  mask2;
1511         private int  shift;
1512 
1513         private final Surrogate.Parser sgp = new Surrogate.Parser();
1514 
1515         public Encoder(Charset cs) {
1516             super(cs, 2.0f, 2.0f);
1517             mask1 = 0xFFF8;
1518             mask2 = 0x0007;
1519             shift = 3;
1520         }
1521 
1522         protected Encoder(Charset cs, String modIdx2a) {
1523             super(cs, 2.0f, 2.0f);
1524             mask1 = 0xFFF8;
1525             mask2 = 0x0007;
1526             shift = 3;
1527             index1 = index1;
1528             index2 = index2;
1529             index2a = modIdx2a;
1530         }
1531 
1532         /**
1533          * Returns true if the given character can be converted to the
1534          * target character encoding.
1535          */
1536 
1537         public boolean canEncode(char ch) {
1538            int  index;
1539            int  theBytes;
1540 
1541            index = index1[((ch & mask1) >> shift)] + (ch & mask2);
1542            if (index < 15000)
1543              theBytes = (int)(index2.charAt(index));
1544            else
1545              theBytes = (int)(index2a.charAt(index-15000));
1546 
1547            if (theBytes != 0)
1548               return (true);
1549 
1550            // only return true if input char was unicode null - all others are
1551            //    undefined
1552            return( ch == '\u0000');
1553         }
1554 
1555         private CoderResult encodeArrayLoop(CharBuffer src, ByteBuffer dst) {
1556             char[] sa = src.array();
1557             int sp = src.arrayOffset() + src.position();
1558             int sl = src.arrayOffset() + src.limit();
1559             byte[] da = dst.array();
1560             int dp = dst.arrayOffset() + dst.position();
1561             int dl = dst.arrayOffset() + dst.limit();
1562             int outputSize = 0;         // size of output
1563             byte[] outputBytes = new byte[2];
1564 
1565             boolean needsFlushing = false;
1566 
1567             try {
1568                 while (sp < sl) {
1569                 char inputChar = sa[sp];
1570 
1571                 // Reject surrogates
1572                 if (sgp.parse(inputChar, sa, sp, sl) < 0)
1573                     return sgp.error();
1574                 if (Surrogate.is(inputChar))
1575                         return sgp.unmappableResult();
1576 
1577                 switch (charState) {
1578                 case G0:
1579                     l = LBase;
1580                     v = VBase;
1581                     t = TBase;
1582 
1583                     if ( isLeadingC(inputChar) ) {     // Leading Consonant
1584                         l = inputChar;
1585                         charState = G1;
1586                         break;
1587                     }
1588 
1589                     if ( isVowel(inputChar) ) {        // Vowel
1590                         v = inputChar;
1591                         charState = G2;
1592                         break;
1593                     }
1594 
1595                     if ( isTrailingC(inputChar) ) {    // Trailing Consonant
1596                         t = inputChar;
1597                         charState = G3;
1598                         break;
1599                     }
1600 
1601                     break;
1602 
1603                     case G1:
1604                         if ( isLeadingC(inputChar) ) {     // Leading Consonant
1605                             l = composeLL(l, inputChar);
1606                             needsFlushing = true;
1607                         break;
1608                         }
1609 
1610                         if ( isVowel(inputChar) ) {        // Vowel
1611                             v = inputChar;
1612                             charState = G2;
1613                             needsFlushing = true;
1614                             break;
1615                         }
1616 
1617                         if ( isTrailingC(inputChar) ) {    // Trailing Consonant
1618                             t = inputChar;
1619                             charState = G3;
1620                             needsFlushing = true;
1621                             break;
1622                         }
1623 
1624                         charState = G0;
1625                         break;
1626 
1627                     case G2:
1628                         if ( isLeadingC(inputChar) ) {     // Leading Consonant
1629                             needsFlushing = true;
1630 
1631                             l = inputChar;
1632                             v = VBase;
1633                             t = TBase;
1634                             charState = G1;
1635                             break;
1636                         }
1637 
1638                         if ( isVowel(inputChar) ) {        // Vowel
1639                             needsFlushing = true;
1640                             v = composeVV(l, inputChar);
1641                             charState = G2;
1642                             break;
1643                         }
1644 
1645                         if ( isTrailingC(inputChar) ) {    // Trailing Consonant
1646                             needsFlushing = true;
1647                             t = inputChar;
1648                             charState = G3;
1649                             break;
1650                         }
1651 
1652                         charState = G0;
1653                         break;
1654 
1655                     case G3:
1656                         if ( isTrailingC(inputChar) ) {    // Trailing Consonant
1657                             needsFlushing = true;
1658                             t = composeTT(t, inputChar);
1659                             charState = G3;
1660                             break;
1661                         }
1662 
1663                         charState = G0;
1664                         break;
1665                   }
1666 
1667                   if (charState == G0 || sl - sp < 2) {
1668                       int spaceNeeded;
1669 
1670                       if (needsFlushing) {
1671                         needsFlushing = false;
1672 
1673                         outputBytes = encodeHangul(composeHangul());
1674 
1675                         if (outputBytes[0] == 0x00 && outputBytes[1] == 0x00
1676                             && inputChar != '\u0000') {
1677                             return CoderResult.unmappableForLength(1);
1678                         }
1679 
1680                         if (outputBytes[0] == 0x00)
1681                             spaceNeeded = 1;
1682                         else
1683                             spaceNeeded = 2;
1684 
1685                         if (dl - dp < spaceNeeded)
1686                              return CoderResult.OVERFLOW;
1687                           if (spaceNeeded == 1)
1688                                 da[dp++] = outputBytes[1];
1689                           else {
1690                                 da[dp++] = outputBytes[0];
1691                                 da[dp++] = outputBytes[1];
1692                           }
1693                       }
1694 
1695                       outputBytes = encodeHangul(inputChar);
1696 
1697                       if (outputBytes[0] == 0x00 && outputBytes[1] == 0x00
1698                           && inputChar != '\u0000') {
1699                           return CoderResult.unmappableForLength(1);
1700                       }
1701 
1702                       if (outputBytes[0] == 0x00)
1703                           spaceNeeded = 1;
1704                       else
1705                           spaceNeeded = 2;
1706 
1707                       if (dl - dp < spaceNeeded)
1708                             return CoderResult.OVERFLOW;
1709 
1710                       if (spaceNeeded == 1)
1711                             da[dp++] = outputBytes[1];
1712                       else {
1713                             da[dp++] = outputBytes[0];
1714                             da[dp++] = outputBytes[1];
1715                         }
1716                     }
1717                   sp++;
1718                 }
1719                 return CoderResult.UNDERFLOW;
1720             } finally {
1721                 src.position(sp - src.arrayOffset());
1722                 dst.position(dp - dst.arrayOffset());
1723             }
1724         }
1725 
1726         private CoderResult encodeBufferLoop(CharBuffer src, ByteBuffer dst) {
1727             int mark = src.position();
1728             int outputSize = 0;
1729             byte[] outputBytes = new byte[2];
1730             boolean needsFlushing = false;
1731 
1732             try {
1733                 while (src.hasRemaining()) {
1734                     char inputChar = src.get();
1735                     if (Surrogate.is(inputChar)) {
1736                         if (sgp.parse(inputChar, src) < 0)
1737                             return sgp.error();
1738                     return sgp.unmappableResult();
1739                     }
1740 
1741                     if (inputChar >= '\uFFFE')
1742                         return CoderResult.unmappableForLength(1);
1743 
1744                     switch (charState) {
1745                     case G0:
1746                         l = LBase;
1747                         v = VBase;
1748                         t = TBase;
1749 
1750                         if ( isLeadingC(inputChar) ) {     // Leading Consonant
1751                             l = inputChar;
1752                             charState = G1;
1753                             break;
1754                         }
1755 
1756                         if ( isVowel(inputChar) ) {        // Vowel
1757                             v = inputChar;
1758                             charState = G2;
1759                             break;
1760                         }
1761 
1762                         if ( isTrailingC(inputChar) ) {    // Trailing Consonant
1763                             t = inputChar;
1764                             charState = G3;
1765                             break;
1766                         }
1767 
1768                         break;
1769 
1770                         case G1:
1771                             if ( isLeadingC(inputChar) ) {     // Leading Consonant
1772                                 l = composeLL(l, inputChar);
1773                                 needsFlushing = true;
1774                             break;
1775                             }
1776 
1777                             if ( isVowel(inputChar) ) {        // Vowel
1778                                 v = inputChar;
1779                                 charState = G2;
1780                                 needsFlushing = true;
1781                                 break;
1782                             }
1783 
1784                             if ( isTrailingC(inputChar) ) {    // Trailing Consonant
1785                                 t = inputChar;
1786                                 charState = G3;
1787                                 needsFlushing = true;
1788                                 break;
1789                             }
1790 
1791                             charState = G0;
1792                             break;
1793 
1794                         case G2:
1795                             if ( isLeadingC(inputChar) ) {     // Leading Consonant
1796                                 needsFlushing = true;
1797 
1798                                 l = inputChar;
1799                                 v = VBase;
1800                                 t = TBase;
1801                                 charState = G1;
1802                                 break;
1803                             }
1804 
1805                             if ( isVowel(inputChar) ) {        // Vowel
1806                                 needsFlushing = true;
1807                                 v = composeVV(l, inputChar);
1808                                 charState = G2;
1809                                 break;
1810                             }
1811 
1812                             if ( isTrailingC(inputChar) ) {    // Trailing Consonant
1813                                 needsFlushing = true;
1814                                 t = inputChar;
1815                                 charState = G3;
1816                                 break;
1817                             }
1818 
1819                             charState = G0;
1820                             break;
1821 
1822                         case G3:
1823                             if ( isTrailingC(inputChar) ) {    // Trailing Consonant
1824                                 needsFlushing = true;
1825                                 t = composeTT(t, inputChar);
1826                                 charState = G3;
1827                                 break;
1828                             }
1829 
1830                             charState = G0;
1831                             break;
1832                       }
1833 
1834                       if (charState == G0 || src.remaining() <= 0) {
1835                           int spaceNeeded;
1836 
1837                           if (needsFlushing) {
1838                             needsFlushing = false;
1839 
1840                             outputBytes = encodeHangul(composeHangul());
1841                             if (outputBytes[0] == 0x00
1842                                 && outputBytes[1] == 0x00
1843                                 && inputChar != '\u0000') {
1844                                 return CoderResult.unmappableForLength(1);
1845                             }
1846                             if (outputBytes[0] == 0x00)
1847                                 spaceNeeded = 1;
1848                             else
1849                                 spaceNeeded = 2;
1850 
1851                             if (dst.remaining() < spaceNeeded)
1852                                  return CoderResult.OVERFLOW;
1853                               if (spaceNeeded == 1)
1854                                     dst.put(outputBytes[1]);
1855                               else {
1856                                     dst.put(outputBytes[0]);
1857                                     dst.put(outputBytes[1]);
1858                               }
1859                           }
1860 
1861                           outputBytes = encodeHangul(inputChar);
1862                           if (outputBytes[0] == 0x00 && outputBytes[1] == 0x00
1863                               && inputChar != '\u0000') {
1864                               return CoderResult.unmappableForLength(1);
1865                           }
1866                           if (outputBytes[0] == 0x00)
1867                               spaceNeeded = 1;
1868                           else
1869                               spaceNeeded = 2;
1870 
1871                           if (dst.remaining() < spaceNeeded)
1872                                 return CoderResult.OVERFLOW;
1873 
1874                           if (spaceNeeded == 1)
1875                                 dst.put(outputBytes[1]);
1876                           else {
1877                                 dst.put(outputBytes[0]);
1878                                 dst.put(outputBytes[1]);
1879                             }
1880                         }
1881                       mark++;
1882                 }
1883                 return CoderResult.UNDERFLOW;
1884             } finally {
1885                 src.position(mark);
1886             }
1887         }
1888 
1889         protected void implReset() {
1890             charState = G0;
1891         }
1892 
1893         private char composeHangul() {
1894            int lIndex, vIndex, tIndex;
1895 
1896            lIndex = l - LBase;
1897            vIndex = v - VBase;
1898            tIndex = t - TBase;
1899 
1900            return (char)((lIndex * VCount + vIndex) * TCount + tIndex + SBase);
1901         }
1902 
1903         private char composeLL(char l1, char l2) {
1904            return l2;
1905         }
1906 
1907         private char composeVV(char v1, char v2) {
1908            return v2;
1909         }
1910 
1911         private char composeTT(char t1, char t2) {
1912            return t2;
1913         }
1914 
1915         private boolean isLeadingC(char c) {
1916            return (c >= LBase && c <= '\u1159');
1917         }
1918 
1919         private boolean isVowel(char c) {
1920            return (c >= VBase && c <= '\u11a2');
1921         }
1922 
1923         private boolean isTrailingC(char c) {
1924            return (c >= TBase && c <= '\u11f9');
1925         }
1926 
1927         private byte[] encodeHangul(char unicode) {
1928             int index;
1929             byte[] outputBytes = new byte[2];
1930 
1931             int theBytes;
1932 
1933             // first we convert the unicode to its byte representation
1934 
1935             index = index1[((unicode & mask1) >> shift)] + (unicode & mask2);
1936             if (index < 15000)
1937              theBytes = (int)(index2.charAt(index));
1938             else
1939              theBytes = (int)(index2a.charAt(index-15000));
1940 
1941             outputBytes[0] = (byte)((theBytes & 0x0000ff00)>>8);
1942             outputBytes[1] = (byte)(theBytes & 0x000000ff);
1943 
1944             return outputBytes;
1945         }
